text: Stanwix is a populated place situated in Maricopa County, Arizona. Settled in 1858, it was originally called The Dutchmans. By 1860 it was known as Stanwix Station, named for a local settler. It has also been called Grinnell Station and Stanvix Hall at other points in history.
